}}'''American Apparel Inc.'''是一家网上服裝零售商以及前[[实体店|实体]]服裝零售商，总部位于美国[[加利福尼亚州|加利福尼亚州]][[洛杉矶|洛杉矶]]。公司由加拿大商人{{link-en|達夫·查尼|Dov Charney}}于1989年创立，該公司採取[[垂直整合|垂直整合]]模式，是北美最大的服装制造商和零售商之一<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.wsj.com/articles/american-apparel-wins-final-loan-approval-1446483056|title=American Apparel Wins Final Loan Approval|author=Gleason|first=Stephanie|date=2 November 2015|work=Wall Street Journal|accessdate=3 November 2015|archive-date=2021-04-10|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210410071633/https://www.wsj.com/articles/american-apparel-wins-final-loan-approval-1446483056}}</ref>。

在连续6年亏损后<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.independent.co.uk/news/business/news/american-apparel-files-for-bankruptcy-in-the-us-a6679621.html|title=American Apparel files for bankruptcy in the US|author=Hutchison|first=Clare|date=5 October 2015|work=The Independent|accessdate=3 November 2015|archive-date=2018-06-30|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180630014403/https://www.independent.co.uk/news/business/news/american-apparel-files-for-bankruptcy-in-the-us-a6679621.html}}</ref>，American Apparel于2015年10月5日在美国[[加利福尼亚州|加利福尼亚州]]中区破产法院申请[[破產保護|破产保护]] <ref name="Zoe Thomas">{{Cite news|author=Thomas|first=Zoe|url=https://www.bbc.com/news/world-us-canada-34450061|title=Will bankruptcy cost American Apparel its cool?|work=BBC News|date=5 October 2015|accessdate=5 October 2015|archive-date=2021-04-10|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210410071629/https://www.bbc.com/news/world-us-canada-34450061}}</ref> <ref>{{Cite web|title=American Apparel, Once Worth Nearly $1 Billion, Is Now Bankrupt|url=https://abcnews.go.com/Business/american-apparel-worth-billion-now-bankrupt/story?id=34263639|author=Kim|first=Susanna|work=ABC News|access-date=2021-04-10|archive-date=2021-05-11|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210511014707/https://abcnews.go.com/Business/american-apparel-worth-billion-now-bankrupt/story?id=34263639}}</ref> <ref>{{Cite web|title=American Apparel Chapter 11 Voluntary Petition|url=https://www.pacermonitor.com/view/3TUJYZQ/American_Apparel_Inc__debke-15-12055__0001.0.pdf|accessdate=16 May 2016|work=PacerMonitor|publisher=PacerMonitor|archive-date=2017-11-07|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171107113052/https://www.pacermonitor.com/view/3TUJYZQ/American_Apparel_Inc__debke-15-12055__0001.0.pdf}}</ref>。据悉该品牌随后与[[债权人|债权人]]达成了一项计划，将2亿美元的[[债务|债务]]转化为[[股權|股权]]（債轉股）<ref>{{Cite news|author=Lindsay|first=Whipp|url=http://www.ft.com/cms/s/0/93f173b8-6b56-11e5-8171-ba1968cf791a.html#axzz3tdJyg9Ps|title=American Apparel is forced to refashion its business|work=[[金融时报_(英国)|金融时报 (英国)]]|date=5 October 2015|accessdate=7 December 2015|archive-date=2016-08-02|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160802091048/http://www.ft.com/cms/s/0/93f173b8-6b56-11e5-8171-ba1968cf791a.html#axzz3tdJyg9Ps}}</ref>。在其資產重组计划被特拉华州破产法院接受后，该公司正式退出破产，并由债权人和债券持有人持有，公司所有的前股东以及前CEO和创始人達夫·查尼不再擁有該公司。2016年11月，American Apparel第二次申请破产。2017年1月，{{link-en|Gildan Activewear}}在American Apparel破产拍卖中以8800万美元的价格购买了American Apparel的知识产权和其他资产<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.chicagotribune.com/business/ct-american-apparel-bankruptcy-deal-future-20170110-story.html|title=American Apparel bankruptcy deal leaves retail future in doubt|author=Church|first=Matt Townsend, Sandrine Rastello and Steven|work=chicagotribune.com|accessdate=2017-01-10|archive-date=2020-07-27|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200727062857/https://www.chicagotribune.com/business/ct-american-apparel-bankruptcy-deal-future-20170110-story.html}}</ref>。

2017年1月，American Apparel裁减了2400名[[南加利福尼亞州|南加利福尼亞州]]工人，并根據[[美国破产法第七章|美国破产法第七章]]关闭公司工厂以及110家门店<ref>{{Cite news|first=Shan|author=Li|url=https://www.latimes.com/business/la-fi-american-apparel-layoffs-20170116-story.html|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170117002111/http://www.latimes.com/business/la-fi-american-apparel-layoffs-20170116-story.html|archivedate=2017-01-17|title=American Apparel starts mass layoffs as company winds down operations|work=[[洛杉磯時報|洛杉磯時報]]|date=2017-01-16|accessdate=2017-01-17}}</ref>。

截至2017年年中，American Apparel以线上零售商的形式运营，其大部分产品均为国际制造。其大部分服装都来自中美洲的工厂，主要來源國為[[洪都拉斯|洪都拉斯]]和[[尼加拉瓜|尼加拉瓜]]<ref name="Guardian-AA-Honduras">{{Cite news|author=Ibrahim|first=Noor|date=2017-11-12|title=The new American Apparel: claims of 'ethically made' abroad clash with reality|url=https://www.theguardian.com/business/2017/nov/12/the-new-american-apparel-claims-of-ethically-made-abroad-clash-with-reality|work=The Guardian|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20190917231226/https://www.theguardian.com/business/2017/nov/12/the-new-american-apparel-claims-of-ethically-made-abroad-clash-with-reality|archivedate=2019-11-17|accessdate=2020-05-24|quote=American Apparel then reopened as an online-only retailer, and by February, it swapped its “Made in USA” mantra with the phrase “Globally-Sourced,” as most of its apparel is now sourced from factories based in Central America, primarily in Honduras.}}</ref> <ref name="QZ-AA-Outside-America">{{Cite news|author=Bain|first=Marc|date=April 7, 2017|title=American Apparel is making its first products outside America|url=https://qz.com/953308/american-apparel-owned-by-gildan-gil-is-making-its-first-products-outside-america/|work=qz.com|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20210410071643/https://qz.com/953308/american-apparel-owned-by-gildan-gil-is-making-its-first-products-outside-america/|quote=For the first time, however, products bearing the American Apparel name will have tags that read “Made in Honduras” and “Made in Nicaragua.”|accessdate=2021-04-10|archive-date=2021-04-10}}</ref>。

